---
// Figure: Alternative access is a separate threat model
// Three simple routes (digital, assisted, human) × three rows
// (verification method, support model, privacy risk).
// Point: each route is its own design problem, not a fallback.
---

<div class="reveal my-12 md:my-16">
  <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border overflow-hidden" style="background: rgba(11,11,17,0.6);">
    <div class="p-6 md:p-8">

      <div class="mb-6">
        <p class="text-text-tertiary text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.2em] uppercase mb-1">Access design</p>
        <h3 class="text-text-primary font-display font-bold text-lg tracking-tight">Alternative access is a separate threat model</h3>
      </div>

      <!-- Column headers -->
      <div class="grid grid-cols-[8rem,1fr,1fr,1fr] gap-3 mb-3 pb-3 border-b border-border/50">
        <div></div>
        <div class="text-center">
          <p class="text-xs font-display font-semibold text-text-primary">Digital route</p>
        </div>
        <div class="text-center">
          <p class="text-xs font-display font-semibold text-text-primary">Assisted route</p>
        </div>
        <div class="text-center">
          <p class="text-xs font-display font-semibold text-text-primary">Human route</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="divide-y divide-border/40 text-sm">

        <!-- Row: Verification method -->
        <div class="grid grid-cols-[8rem,1fr,1fr,1fr] gap-3 py-3 md:py-4">
          <div class="text-[11px] font-semibold tracking-[0.12em] uppercase text-text-tertiary pt-1">Verification method</div>
          <div class="text-text-secondary text-xs md:text-sm leading-snug">Cryptographic check on a live endpoint.</div>
          <div class="text-text-secondary text-xs md:text-sm leading-snug">Digitised check via a signed code or QR.</div>
          <div class="text-text-secondary text-xs md:text-sm leading-snug">Protocolised officer check against defined evidence.</div>
        </div>

        <!-- Row: Support model -->
        <div class="grid grid-cols-[8rem,1fr,1fr,1fr] gap-3 py-3 md:py-4">
          <div class="text-[11px] font-semibold tracking-[0.12em] uppercase text-text-tertiary pt-1">Support model</div>
          <div class="text-text-secondary text-xs md:text-sm leading-snug">Self service with helpline escalation.</div>
          <div class="text-text-secondary text-xs md:text-sm leading-snug">Face to face help at point of use.</div>
          <div class="text-text-secondary text-xs md:text-sm leading-snug">Dedicated casework for people the system will otherwise fail.</div>
        </div>

        <!-- Row: Privacy risk -->
        <div class="grid grid-cols-[8rem,1fr,1fr,1fr] gap-3 py-3 md:py-4">
          <div class="text-[11px] font-semibold tracking-[0.12em] uppercase text-text-tertiary pt-1">Privacy risk</div>
          <div class="text-text-secondary text-xs md:text-sm leading-snug">Retention and linkage across relying parties.</div>
          <div class="text-text-secondary text-xs md:text-sm leading-snug">Replay of codes · over-disclosure at the counter.</div>
          <div class="text-text-secondary text-xs md:text-sm leading-snug">Casework records that outlast their purpose.</div>
        </div>

      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
  <p class="text-text-tertiary text-xs mt-3 text-center italic">
    Each route is a separate design problem, not a degraded fallback.
  </p>
</div>
